      <gmd:lineage>
        <gmd:LI_Lineage>
          <gmd:statement>
            <gco:CharacterString>Regional councils are based on the meshblock pattern. 
Non-alignment of meshblock and cadastral boundaries are one of a number of reasons for meshblock boundary adjustments. Other reasons include requests from local authorities, Local Government Commission, Electoral Representation Commission and to make census enumeration processes easier.
From the meshblock pattern, higher geographies, including the 2022 regional council pattern, were dissolved using the dissolve tool in the Arc GIS suite.</gco:CharacterString>
          </gmd:statement>
        </gmd:LI_Lineage>
